To add Tags Fn

- models.py 
    - have tag class
    - Update Tweet model , Add tags field
        - related_name="tweets_tag_set" allows tag.tweets_tag_set.all() to get all tweets with a tag.
    - In tweet model we have a save fun for tags to save them 

- admin.py
    - add tag class from model to admin

- make a file of custom tag filter (tweet_tags.py)
- in html we Load the filter in your template and use {{ tweet.text|truncatewords:35|render_hashtags|safe }}   , here render_hashtags is the filter we made that make tags in text clickable and blue   

- Make a view for tag in views.py And URL in urls.py

